description: Aztec Minerals Corp. acquires, explores for, and evaluates mineral resources in Canada, Mexico, and the United States. The company primarily explores for gold, copper, silver, lead, and zinc deposits. It holds interest in the Cervantes porphyry gold-copper property covering an area of 3,650 hectares located in Sonora, Mexico. The company was incorporated in 2007 and is headquartered in Vancouver, Canada.
ceo: Mr. Simon Christopher Dyakowski C.F.A., M.B.A.
